"{\"uid\": \"ibj.com-articles-gretchen-walsh-follows-world-record-with-1st-olympic-berth-carson-foster-wins-400-im\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Gretchen Walsh followed up a world record in the 100-meter butterfly with something that felt just as good.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 107, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 14, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gretchen_Walsh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gretchen Walsh\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gretchen_Walsh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gretchen_Walsh\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Her first trip to the Olympics.\", \"from\": 109, \"to\": 140, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Walsh did not go quite as fast as a night earlier in the semifinals, but she touched in 55.31 seconds to claim the coveted Olympic berth against a loaded field at the U.S. Olympic swimming trials on Sunday.\", \"from\": 142, \"to\": 348, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"On the second night of the trials at Lucas Oil Stadium in Indianapolis, Carson Foster made up for the disappointment of 2021, when he just missed out on the Olympics, with a victory in the men's 400-meter individual medley.\", \"from\": 350, \"to\": 573, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 408, \"end\": 420, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indianapolis\", \"score\": 0.9999999999772626, \"rank\": 1.905356881843841e-11, \"text\": \"Indianapolis\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indianapolis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indianapolis\"}, {\"begin\": 422, \"end\": 435, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carson_Foster\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Carson Foster\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carson_Foster\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carson_Foster\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And 30-year-old Nic Fink, whose wife is expecting a child, made it quite a Father's Day by winning the 100-meter breaststroke.\", \"from\": 575, \"to\": 701, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 591, \"end\": 599, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nic_Fink\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nic Fink\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nic_Fink\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nic_Fink\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Looking into the stands toward Melanie Margolis Fink-herself a gold medalist at the 2016 Rio Games-he made a rocking motion.\", \"from\": 703, \"to\": 827, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Clearly, Nic Fink's mind was on more than just a gold of his own.\", \"from\": 829, \"to\": 894, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 838, \"end\": 846, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nic_Fink\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nic Fink\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nic_Fink\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nic_Fink\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Women's 100-meter butterfly final  Facing three medalists from the Tokyo Games, Walsh knew she had her work cut out for her-even after setting a world record in the semifinals with a time of 55.18 that broke the mark held by Sweden's Sarah Sj\\u00f6str\\u00f6m since the 2016 Rio de Janeiro Olympics.\", \"from\": 896, \"to\": 1184, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1121, \"end\": 1127, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sweden_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9841051412354215, \"rank\": 0.011804946091955216, \"text\": \"Sweden\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sweden_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sweden_women's_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1130, \"end\": 1144, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sarah_Sj\\u00f6str\\u00f6m\", \"score\": 0.9999994657338511, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sarah Sj\\u00f6str\\u00f6m\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sarah_Sj\\u00f6str\\u00f6m\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sarah_Sj\\u00f6str\\u00f6m\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Following the same strategy, Walsh went out strong again in the final and was under her world-record pace at the turn.\", \"from\": 1186, \"to\": 1304, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Then, it was a matter of hanging on for the 21-year-old native of Nashville, Tennessee, who swims for the University of Virginia.\", \"from\": 1306, \"to\": 1435, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1383, \"end\": 1392, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tennessee_Volunteers\", \"score\": 0.9963628209507669, \"rank\": 0.0033442639285103898, \"text\": \"Tennessee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tennessee_Volunteers\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tennessee_Volunteers\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She finished with the second-fastest time in history, while Torri Huske grabbed the second Olympic spot with a time of 55.52 that made her the third-fastest woman in swimming history.\", \"from\": 1437, \"to\": 1620, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1497, \"end\": 1508, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Torri_Huske\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Torri Huske\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Torri_Huske\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Torri_Huske\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I could not ask for a better start to the meet,\\\" Walsh said.\", \"from\": 1622, \"to\": 1683, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Regan Smith became the fourth-fastest female ever at 55.62-but the third-place showing wasn't enough to get her to Paris on the powerhouse American team.\", \"from\": 1685, \"to\": 1838, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1685, \"end\": 1696, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Regan_Smith\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.4314095499569574e-42, \"text\": \"Regan Smith\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Regan_Smith\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Regan_Smith\"}, {\"begin\": 1800, \"end\": 1805, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999988181116, \"rank\": 1.1817160150031485e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1824, \"end\": 1832, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.8785109904498191, \"rank\": 0.13717390806336774, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She will have more chances later in the meet to claim her spot.\", \"from\": 1839, \"to\": 1902, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Kelly Pashof Carmel finished fifth in the final with a time of 57.72.\", \"from\": 1904, \"to\": 1973, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1904, \"end\": 1909, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Osbourne\", \"score\": 0.9999999999986358, \"rank\": 1.5143941716432518e-12, \"text\": \"Kelly\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Osbourne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Osbourne\"}, {\"begin\": 1917, \"end\": 1923, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carmel_McQueen\", \"score\": 0.9999999953824954, \"rank\": 4.6177076596579224e-09, \"text\": \"Carmel\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carmel_McQueen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carmel_McQueen\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Alex Shackellof the Carmel Swim Club, who qualified fourth for the event, was a late scratch for the race, but she swam in the women's 200-meter freestyle semifinals, finishing sixth in 1:57.42 to qualify for Monday night's final.\", \"from\": 1975, \"to\": 2205, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1975, \"end\": 1979, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Rousseau\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.492187632065068e-15, \"text\": \"Alex\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Rousseau\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Rousseau\"}, {\"begin\": 1995, \"end\": 2001, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carmel_McQueen\", \"score\": 0.9999999953824954, \"rank\": 4.6177076596579224e-09, \"text\": \"Carmel\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carmel_McQueen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carmel_McQueen\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Men's 400-meter individual medley  The first final of the night produced another first-time Olympian when Foster knocked off Tokyo gold medalist Chase Kalisz.\", \"from\": 2207, \"to\": 2365, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2299, \"end\": 2307, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999949218956105, \"rank\": 5.0781303551372285e-06, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}, {\"begin\": 2313, \"end\": 2319, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Myles_Birket_Foster\", \"score\": 0.9999999996762199, \"rank\": 3.239326778817277e-10, \"text\": \"Foster\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Myles_Birket_Foster\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Myles_Birket_Foster\"}, {\"begin\": 2332, \"end\": 2337, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999999446868075, \"rank\": 5.53128531192636e-08, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 2352, \"end\": 2364, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chase_Kalisz\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chase Kalisz\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chase_Kalisz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chase_Kalisz\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Kalisz should get a chance to defend his gold in Paris, taking the runner-up spot to claim the expected second American slot.\", \"from\": 2367, \"to\": 2496, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2371, \"end\": 2377, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kalisz\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.215658065273843e-15, \"text\": \"Kalisz\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kalisz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kalisz\"}, {\"begin\": 2420, \"end\": 2425, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999988181116, \"rank\": 1.1817160150031485e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2482, \"end\": 2490, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.8785109904498191, \"rank\": 0.13717390806336774, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jay Litherland, the 400 IM silver medalist in Tokyo, missed out on his third Olympics with a third-place showing.\", \"from\": 2498, \"to\": 2611, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2498, \"end\": 2512, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jay_Litherland\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jay Litherland\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jay_Litherland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jay_Litherland\"}, {\"begin\": 2544, \"end\